WEBVTT

00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:39.893
Yesterday...

00:00:39.893 --> 00:00:41.058
Yesterday?

00:00:41.058 --> 00:00:42.517
We kissed.

00:00:42.517 --> 00:00:43.570
What?

00:00:43.570 --> 00:00:46.558
I was so jittery about seeing you again
that sleep completely escaped me.

00:00:46.558 --> 00:00:49.671
Did you manage to get any rest?

00:00:51.876 --> 00:00:53.733
Ui Yeong, is it true?

00:00:53.733 --> 00:00:56.673
Did you kiss?

00:00:56.673 --> 00:00:57.803
Yeah, we did.

00:00:57.803 --> 00:01:02.274
But... Do I really have to admit that publicly?

00:01:02.274 --> 00:01:03.851
Are you going to stay here?

00:01:03.851 --> 00:01:07.457
We have something important to discuss.

00:01:17.844 --> 00:01:22.310
[Episode 5]

00:01:23.063 --> 00:01:25.341
What's so important?

00:01:25.341 --> 00:01:27.543
Wait...

00:01:28.476 --> 00:01:30.240
We may have missed each other before,

00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:32.450
but we ended up meeting again.

00:01:32.450 --> 00:01:34.867
- And we kissed.
- Once I decide something isn't right,

00:01:34.867 --> 00:01:36.891
- The way he's wrapping this up...
- I don't go back on it.

00:01:36.891 --> 00:01:38.369
sounds exactly like a confession.

00:01:38.369 --> 00:01:39.589
What should we do?

00:01:39.589 --> 00:01:43.495
Should we just start dating
and see how it goes?

00:01:43.495 --> 00:01:45.398
Ms. Ui Yeong?

00:01:45.398 --> 00:01:48.284
I meant we should work together.

00:01:48.284 --> 00:01:52.463
Oh, what did you say?

00:01:53.217 --> 00:01:57.763
Eun Ho brought this yesterday
when he dropped off the luggage.

00:01:58.801 --> 00:02:02.758
Sua's really good at drawing.

00:02:02.758 --> 00:02:04.229
But why...

00:02:04.229 --> 00:02:08.175
Oh, she drew on it.

00:02:15.761 --> 00:02:17.938
It sounded like a losing deal for the hotel.

00:02:17.938 --> 00:02:20.202
They even agreed to run the pop-up

00:02:20.202 --> 00:02:22.523
within the concept and budget we proposed.

00:02:22.523 --> 00:02:24.214
And I liked their new idea even more,

00:02:24.214 --> 00:02:26.612
[Deluxe Double Room & Signature Furniture]
creating package rooms featuring the furniture.

00:02:26.612 --> 00:02:29.149
This way,
guests can naturally try out the furniture.

00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:32.695
For furniture makers,
it is not about how pretty it looks.

00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:35.549
We always want people to know
how sturdy it really is.

00:02:35.549 --> 00:02:37.721
I see.

00:02:38.822 --> 00:02:40.460
About that day,

00:02:40.460 --> 00:02:43.118
I'm sorry I got angry

00:02:43.118 --> 00:02:44.809
without even hearing you out.

00:02:44.809 --> 00:02:45.934
You don't have to apologize.

00:02:45.934 --> 00:02:49.508
I'm really grateful that you changed your mind.

00:02:49.508 --> 00:02:52.494
Let's work well together from now on.

00:02:52.494 --> 00:02:53.539
- Okay.
- Then,

00:02:53.539 --> 00:02:55.484
let's get the concept approved by the brand

00:02:55.484 --> 00:02:57.384
and move straight into the kickoff meeting.

00:02:57.384 --> 00:03:00.925
How does your schedule look?
The sooner the better for us.

00:03:00.925 --> 00:03:02.755
Should we check our schedules?

00:03:02.755 --> 00:03:05.068
Sounds good.

00:03:06.703 --> 00:03:09.277
We're ready anytime.

00:03:09.277 --> 00:03:11.266
Maybe Monday?

00:03:13.099 --> 00:03:14.836
Alright then, take care.

00:03:14.836 --> 00:03:17.638
Ms. Ui Yeong, well...

00:03:18.539 --> 00:03:21.031
The ki...

00:03:21.031 --> 00:03:22.581
The ki...

00:03:22.581 --> 00:03:24.153
Key?

00:03:24.153 --> 00:03:25.618
Keyring, no.

00:03:25.618 --> 00:03:28.021
Cream. There's cream on your face, right here.

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:32.053
Maybe from the latte?

00:03:32.053 --> 00:03:34.507
Actually, I mean...

00:03:34.507 --> 00:03:36.294
The...

00:03:36.294 --> 00:03:38.877
K-Key...

00:03:38.877 --> 00:03:40.900
Oh, here it is.

00:03:42.564 --> 00:03:45.141
Oh, okay.

00:03:46.687 --> 00:03:48.364
Alright then, I'll get going.

00:03:48.364 --> 00:03:50.707
Bye.

00:03:55.606 --> 00:03:59.472
But I had a latte.
Why is there cream on my face?

00:04:00.104 --> 00:04:02.337
Come to think of it...

00:04:02.337 --> 00:04:06.557
Is that really how the kiss thing ended?

00:04:09.321 --> 00:04:11.497
I don't know.

00:04:17.941 --> 00:04:20.773
What on earth did I just say?

00:04:22.427 --> 00:04:25.487
They kissed?

00:04:28.639 --> 00:04:32.038
The wood is pretty sensitive.

00:04:32.038 --> 00:04:33.775
Depending on the temperature and humidity,

00:04:33.775 --> 00:04:36.599
it expands and contracts.

00:04:36.599 --> 00:04:41.085
So sometimes the furniture can warp a little.

00:04:42.866 --> 00:04:44.510
- Why?
- Sorry?

00:04:44.510 --> 00:04:45.553
- What?
- What?

00:04:45.553 --> 00:04:46.774
- Oh.
- What do you mean?

00:04:46.774 --> 00:04:48.178
Oh, what I mean is

00:04:48.178 --> 00:04:50.788
we offer free repairs for a year.

00:04:50.788 --> 00:04:53.251
Yeah, that's it.

00:04:53.251 --> 00:04:55.812
Right.

00:04:55.812 --> 00:04:58.864
[After work, let's go to your place.]

00:05:00.878 --> 00:05:03.915
So you really don't need to worry about that.

00:05:03.915 --> 00:05:06.561
Please take your time and have a look around.

00:05:13.531 --> 00:05:15.987
You've got some nerve, man.

00:05:15.987 --> 00:05:17.846
I bet everyone in heaven knows by now.

00:05:17.846 --> 00:05:19.946
How do you kiss someone in a church?

00:05:19.946 --> 00:05:21.911
I wasn't thinking. I swear.

00:05:21.911 --> 00:05:26.127
About the kiss, or telling everyone about it.

00:05:26.127 --> 00:05:28.785
I did it because I wasn't thinking.

00:05:28.785 --> 00:05:30.129
You did well.

00:05:30.129 --> 00:05:31.275
Hey.

00:05:31.275 --> 00:05:33.952
There's no stamp stronger than a kiss.

00:05:33.952 --> 00:05:35.502
You've stamped it already,

00:05:35.502 --> 00:05:37.255
so don't even think about backing out.

00:05:37.255 --> 00:05:38.559
- Uncle.
- Take responsibility...

00:05:38.559 --> 00:05:39.733
Dad.

00:05:39.733 --> 00:05:41.812
What? You were listening?

00:05:41.812 --> 00:05:44.961
Those don't have noise-canceling, remember?

00:05:46.094 --> 00:05:47.379
Sua,

00:05:47.379 --> 00:05:49.371
listen.

00:05:49.371 --> 00:05:52.019
Your uncle here kissed someone.

00:05:52.019 --> 00:05:54.093
Like when you give your dad a peck.

00:05:55.808 --> 00:05:58.582
So are you two in a relationship now?

00:05:58.582 --> 00:06:00.406
- Right.
- But you know,

00:06:00.406 --> 00:06:03.366
that idea is totally outdated, huh?

00:06:03.366 --> 00:06:05.430
What responsibility is there from a kiss?

00:06:05.430 --> 00:06:07.634
Did anyone get hurt? Did something break?

00:06:07.634 --> 00:06:09.154
Well...

00:06:09.154 --> 00:06:11.388
I think your uncle might be a little broken.

00:06:11.388 --> 00:06:14.348
Not broken. Just softer.

00:06:14.348 --> 00:06:17.392
That's what happens when you like someone.

00:06:17.392 --> 00:06:19.629
Yeah, you're right.

00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:21.166
It's been so long I forgot.

00:06:21.166 --> 00:06:22.249
Congrats, Uncle.

00:06:22.249 --> 00:06:25.886
Liking someone is something to celebrate.

00:06:25.886 --> 00:06:28.792
So what are you going to do?

00:06:29.593 --> 00:06:33.569
I should tell her I'll work hard
and do dating properly this time.

00:06:33.569 --> 00:06:34.873
You got this.

00:06:34.873 --> 00:06:36.593
Tell me if something good happens.

00:06:36.593 --> 00:06:38.563
And tell me if you need cheering up too.

00:06:38.563 --> 00:06:42.142
You know we're always on your side.

00:06:51.868 --> 00:06:54.059
Hey, Lee Sua.

00:06:54.059 --> 00:06:56.011
How do you know all this stuff?

00:06:56.011 --> 00:06:59.352
Have you dated before?

00:06:59.352 --> 00:07:01.561
You said those don't have noise canceling, huh?

00:07:01.561 --> 00:07:05.748
Hey, you need my permission to date, okay?

00:07:05.748 --> 00:07:08.961
But I'm not giving permission...

00:07:08.961 --> 00:07:11.608
You're not dating anyone, right?

00:07:37.423 --> 00:07:39.390
This is our division head.

00:07:39.390 --> 00:07:41.180
And these are the representatives from HOME.

00:07:41.180 --> 00:07:44.140
I'm Song Tae Seop.

00:07:44.140 --> 00:07:46.740
I'm Lee Eun Ho.

00:07:51.470 --> 00:07:53.877
We're ready.

00:07:54.530 --> 00:07:56.334
Hello.

00:07:56.334 --> 00:07:58.667
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

00:07:58.667 --> 00:08:00.467
Sir...

00:08:04.177 --> 00:08:06.747
Attorney Kang, it's been a while.

00:08:06.747 --> 00:08:08.227
Hello.

00:08:08.227 --> 00:08:11.937
I heard there was an unpleasant incident
during the bidding process.

00:08:11.937 --> 00:08:14.327
Thank you for accepting the proposal again.

00:08:14.327 --> 00:08:16.091
We've already received a sufficient apology.

00:08:16.091 --> 00:08:19.117
From here on, I hope both companies
can work together on this project.

00:08:19.117 --> 00:08:21.837
We don't hold grudges.

00:08:24.356 --> 00:08:26.380
So, this is the pop-up concept.

00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:28.958
It draws inspiration from a local bar

00:08:28.958 --> 00:08:31.101
that captures the heritage of Deerfiddich,

00:08:31.101 --> 00:08:32.704
a whiskey that has delivered

00:08:32.704 --> 00:08:34.878
the same signature sip for over a century...

00:08:34.878 --> 00:08:36.778
After passing through
a photo zone and mini bar...

00:08:36.778 --> 00:08:38.748
Showcasing the history of Deerfiddich...

00:08:38.748 --> 00:08:40.365
Allowing them to experience the whiskey

00:08:40.365 --> 00:08:43.528
in a more sensory way.

00:08:48.287 --> 00:08:50.224
In the second exhibition zone,

00:08:50.224 --> 00:08:53.031
the actual bottles will be displayed
by aging year,

00:08:53.031 --> 00:08:57.876
with explanations of
each one's character and appeal.

00:08:57.876 --> 00:08:59.900
I'm looking forward to the results.

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:02.211
Please support whatever HOME needs.

00:09:02.211 --> 00:09:02.982
- Yes.
- Got it.

00:09:02.982 --> 00:09:05.590
Thank you.

00:09:05.590 --> 00:09:07.828
Thank you.

00:09:11.614 --> 00:09:12.758
So...

00:09:12.758 --> 00:09:15.061
I told them to take extra care preparing this.

00:09:15.061 --> 00:09:16.092
How is it?

00:09:16.092 --> 00:09:18.241
- It's really good.
- That's a relief.

00:09:18.241 --> 00:09:19.647
Please enjoy.

00:09:19.647 --> 00:09:20.811
By the way,

00:09:20.811 --> 00:09:24.168
what made you change your mind?

00:09:25.911 --> 00:09:28.538
Because of Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:09:32.005 --> 00:09:33.180
Oh, well...

00:09:33.180 --> 00:09:36.220
He tends to keep things short,
so people sometimes misunderstand him.

00:09:36.220 --> 00:09:39.037
What he means is
Ms. Ui Yeong's passion changed our minds.

00:09:39.037 --> 00:09:41.723
That's what he meant.

00:09:41.723 --> 00:09:46.603
I've never seen anyone fold animals
out of towels that well before.

00:09:46.603 --> 00:09:49.553
She really does handle things
with a lot of creativity.

00:09:49.553 --> 00:09:50.607
Yes, she really does.

00:09:50.607 --> 00:09:53.418
So going forward,
I'd like to keep communicating

00:09:53.418 --> 00:09:56.318
through Ms. Ui Yeong as well.

00:09:56.318 --> 00:09:57.541
Yes, that sounds good.

00:09:57.541 --> 00:09:59.988
I'll be the one coordinating with the brand,

00:09:59.988 --> 00:10:02.459
so just keep me updated on the progress.

00:10:02.459 --> 00:10:03.786
Okay.

00:10:03.786 --> 00:10:07.576
Then if you need anything,
please feel free to contact me anytime.

00:10:07.576 --> 00:10:09.521
Sure.

00:10:09.521 --> 00:10:12.321
Please, go ahead and eat.

00:10:14.966 --> 00:10:16.382
We have to work on the pop-up booth

00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:18.913
and the hotel room furniture at the same time,

00:10:18.913 --> 00:10:21.696
so I'm a little worried
the schedule might be tight.

00:10:21.696 --> 00:10:22.966
Yeah, that's true.

00:10:22.966 --> 00:10:25.486
We'll probably be busy for a while,

00:10:25.486 --> 00:10:28.070
so how about we go on dates after work?

00:10:28.070 --> 00:10:30.140
"Dates?"

00:10:32.150 --> 00:10:34.803
- You know we're at work, right?
- Oh, right.

00:10:36.143 --> 00:10:40.077
Good thing no one else heard that.

00:10:40.077 --> 00:10:42.756
So, want to?

00:10:43.455 --> 00:10:45.782
Yeah, I'd like that.

00:10:51.643 --> 00:10:55.040
Hold it together.
Even if you miss him, hold it in.

00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:56.384
You're getting butterflies again?

00:10:56.384 --> 00:10:58.854
You look totally obsessed.

00:10:58.854 --> 00:11:00.266
What?

00:11:00.266 --> 00:11:01.844
Look at this.

00:11:01.844 --> 00:11:03.350
[You're getting butterflies in your celery]
This is pretty fun.

00:11:03.350 --> 00:11:05.461
[You look totally obsessed with melon]

00:11:05.461 --> 00:11:08.579
[Even if you miss grapes, hold it in]
[Hold these cherries]

00:11:08.579 --> 00:11:11.363
Should we grab a coffee
before heading back to the office?

00:11:11.363 --> 00:11:13.743
Sounds good.

00:11:16.115 --> 00:11:17.694
Those spicy chicken feet we had...

00:11:17.694 --> 00:11:19.556
I keep thinking about them.

00:11:19.556 --> 00:11:21.467
At first I was like,

00:11:21.467 --> 00:11:24.459
how do you even eat that?

00:11:24.459 --> 00:11:26.483
They're not really used overseas, right?

00:11:26.483 --> 00:11:29.959
But once you get hooked on that spicy flavor,
there's no going back.

00:11:29.959 --> 00:11:32.218
Take me there again next time. To Eat Eat Club.

00:11:32.218 --> 00:11:34.597
Sure.

00:11:34.597 --> 00:11:36.222
I should get going.

00:11:36.222 --> 00:11:39.112
I'm going to grab some coffee for the team.
Go on ahead.

00:11:39.112 --> 00:11:42.558
- Thanks for today.
- No problem.

00:11:50.311 --> 00:11:51.595
- Yes, Ui Yeong.
- Hyun Min,

00:11:51.595 --> 00:11:53.426
I'm about to grab a coffee
before I head back to the office.

00:11:53.426 --> 00:11:54.792
What do you and Sae Byeok want?

00:11:54.792 --> 00:11:57.263
Then... two iced Americanos, please.

00:11:57.263 --> 00:11:59.441
Oh, and sandwiches too.

00:11:59.441 --> 00:12:01.597
What? You haven't eaten yet?

00:12:01.597 --> 00:12:03.301
Not me. Sae Byeok.

00:12:03.301 --> 00:12:06.361
Skipping meals won't help with mistakes anyway.

00:12:06.361 --> 00:12:07.785
Oh really?

00:12:07.785 --> 00:12:10.941
Alright, got it.

00:12:26.716 --> 00:12:28.713
Are you just getting to work?

00:12:28.713 --> 00:12:31.881
Yeah. Monday through Wednesday,
I work from six to closing.

00:12:31.881 --> 00:12:34.810
Thursday and Friday, from one to six.

00:12:34.810 --> 00:12:36.022
So what,

00:12:36.022 --> 00:12:38.232
you ended up working
with that guy from the blind date?

00:12:38.232 --> 00:12:41.998
Turns out he's involved in the bid
our team submitted.

00:12:41.998 --> 00:12:44.198
Isn't that crazy?

00:12:46.199 --> 00:12:48.135
That's crazy.

00:12:48.135 --> 00:12:50.995
So, are you two dating now?

00:12:52.393 --> 00:12:53.492
No.

00:12:53.492 --> 00:12:55.785
Not that far.

00:12:56.445 --> 00:12:57.484
Right.

00:12:57.484 --> 00:12:58.544
You're not twenty anymore.

00:12:58.544 --> 00:13:01.187
You can't give your whole heart over one kiss.

00:13:01.187 --> 00:13:03.357
I've kissed a lot in my life.

00:13:03.357 --> 00:13:06.725
If you count acting too,
probably five hundred times.

00:13:06.725 --> 00:13:11.287
Once you start attaching meaning to it,
things just get complicated.

00:13:11.287 --> 00:13:14.313
I could even kiss someone
right now if I wanted.

00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:18.187
What are you doing?

00:13:19.867 --> 00:13:22.831
And sure, a kiss isn't everything,

00:13:22.831 --> 00:13:26.364
but it's not nothing either.

00:13:26.364 --> 00:13:28.184
Seriously, how have you been living?

00:13:28.184 --> 00:13:31.157
Just normally.

00:13:35.412 --> 00:13:39.956
So how does it feel riding something like that?

00:13:39.956 --> 00:13:43.807
Like you're cutting through the air.

00:13:43.807 --> 00:13:44.882
"Cutting?"

00:13:44.882 --> 00:13:46.906
If you're curious,
want me to take you for a ride?

00:13:46.906 --> 00:13:48.503
Yeah, sure.

00:13:48.503 --> 00:13:50.676
Next time.

00:13:51.805 --> 00:13:55.091
[Break Room]

00:14:08.212 --> 00:14:11.242
Sae Byeok, your internship ends soon, right?

00:14:11.242 --> 00:14:13.306
I happened to see it
while organizing the contracts.

00:14:13.306 --> 00:14:15.832
Yes. It ends in about a month.

00:14:15.832 --> 00:14:18.242
Honestly, hotels may look glamorous,

00:14:18.242 --> 00:14:22.266
but the pay isn't great
compared to the workload.

00:14:22.266 --> 00:14:24.616
Your starting salary matters a lot.

00:14:24.616 --> 00:14:27.116
I have a close junior who works at a bank.

00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:29.666
If I ask, he could give you some advice.

00:14:29.666 --> 00:14:32.380
Maybe the three of us could meet sometime...

00:14:32.380 --> 00:14:35.306
I'll figure it out myself.

00:14:35.306 --> 00:14:37.047
Okay.

00:14:37.047 --> 00:14:38.877
Where are you? I need to whip you into shape.

00:14:38.877 --> 00:14:39.937
Get to the conference room.

00:14:39.937 --> 00:14:42.940
Ms. Ui Yeong is looking for me,

00:14:42.940 --> 00:14:46.120
- so I'll head over first.
- Sure.

00:14:53.709 --> 00:14:56.332
Are you on a diet these days?

00:14:56.332 --> 00:14:58.902
No, I'm not.

00:14:58.902 --> 00:15:01.539
Then work must be so hard you can't even eat.

00:15:01.539 --> 00:15:04.523
It's okay. Sometimes work really is that tough.

00:15:04.523 --> 00:15:06.480
But you learned something big this time.

00:15:06.480 --> 00:15:09.520
You must've been really disappointed in me.

00:15:09.520 --> 00:15:11.457
Disappointed over one mistake? Come on.

00:15:11.457 --> 00:15:12.750
Then it's time you learn

00:15:12.750 --> 00:15:17.906
how much strength a meal gives you,
even when things are tough.

00:15:17.906 --> 00:15:19.730
Thank you.

00:15:19.730 --> 00:15:22.167
Eat this and get your energy back.
Then help me out.

00:15:22.167 --> 00:15:23.831
- Yeah?
- I'd like you...

00:15:23.831 --> 00:15:26.197
to handle the backup work
for this pop-up project.

00:15:26.197 --> 00:15:28.576
Me?

00:15:28.576 --> 00:15:30.774
But if I do it...

00:15:30.774 --> 00:15:32.387
won't HOME hate that idea?

00:15:32.387 --> 00:15:33.407
If it were me,

00:15:33.407 --> 00:15:35.704
I'd dislike someone who runs away
after making a mistake.

00:15:35.704 --> 00:15:36.911
But someone who takes responsibility
and tries to fix it

00:15:36.911 --> 00:15:39.897
is someone I'd want to work with again.

00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:41.368
Ui Yeong...

00:15:41.368 --> 00:15:43.194
You're going to see it through, right?

00:15:43.194 --> 00:15:46.814
Yes! I'll do it.

00:15:46.814 --> 00:15:49.780
Alright, who's up first?

00:16:02.709 --> 00:16:03.782
I'll keep it short.

00:16:03.782 --> 00:16:04.939
When people stay at a hotel,

00:16:04.939 --> 00:16:07.233
how many actually unpack
and organize their things in the cabinet?

00:16:07.233 --> 00:16:09.735
- Think again. Make it more practical.
- Yes, sir.

00:16:09.735 --> 00:16:12.066
And you two need to check the floor plan again.

00:16:12.066 --> 00:16:13.592
Where do you expect to fit furniture this big?

00:16:13.592 --> 00:16:15.809
Even after staring at it with barely any sleep,

00:16:15.809 --> 00:16:18.450
the room's still small
and the furniture fills it up.

00:16:18.450 --> 00:16:20.660
Sir, this floor plan is like a blank canvas

00:16:20.660 --> 00:16:23.920
with nowhere left to add anything.

00:16:25.954 --> 00:16:28.117
I know it's not an easy job.

00:16:28.117 --> 00:16:29.747
Let's call it a day.

00:16:29.747 --> 00:16:31.508
Head home early and get some rest.

00:16:31.508 --> 00:16:34.074
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

00:17:01.663 --> 00:17:04.260
This is so heavy.

00:17:04.260 --> 00:17:07.966
I'm telling you, it's cheapest online.

00:17:07.966 --> 00:17:10.123
Just search it, sort by minimum order,

00:17:10.123 --> 00:17:12.213
and it gets delivered
to your door the next day.

00:17:12.213 --> 00:17:14.603
I feel better seeing things in person.

00:17:14.603 --> 00:17:16.844
I can check the expiration dates myself

00:17:16.844 --> 00:17:19.665
and catch up with a friend while I'm at it.

00:17:19.665 --> 00:17:21.396
And make your friend carry your stuff too?

00:17:21.396 --> 00:17:25.029
Much appreciated, my friend.

00:17:25.029 --> 00:17:26.062
So?

00:17:26.062 --> 00:17:28.347
What's it like working
with that guy from the blind date?

00:17:28.347 --> 00:17:30.065
Oh, that?

00:17:30.065 --> 00:17:32.451
We just... work.

00:17:32.451 --> 00:17:34.575
I mean, I want to text him first sometimes,

00:17:34.575 --> 00:17:37.115
but I know he's busy, so it feels weird.

00:17:37.115 --> 00:17:39.839
Wouldn't it be nice if he texted me first?

00:17:39.839 --> 00:17:43.158
- After we kissed...
- Wait, what?

00:17:43.158 --> 00:17:45.116
You kissed that guy?

00:17:45.116 --> 00:17:47.866
When?

00:17:47.866 --> 00:17:50.265
Oh, that was before...

00:17:50.265 --> 00:17:52.862
The mood just suddenly got kind of...

00:17:52.862 --> 00:17:55.086
soft and romantic.

00:17:55.086 --> 00:17:57.765
Are you going to nag me about it?

00:17:58.872 --> 00:18:01.250
No, who am I to do that?

00:18:01.250 --> 00:18:02.568
I mean, even I...

00:18:02.568 --> 00:18:04.581
With someone I met through a used item deal...

00:18:04.581 --> 00:18:05.951
What?

00:18:05.951 --> 00:18:08.385
Never mind. Stuff like that happens.

00:18:08.385 --> 00:18:09.672
Ui Yeong, want to work out?

00:18:09.672 --> 00:18:13.101
I literally just worked out. I'm exhausted.

00:18:13.101 --> 00:18:14.848
I'll take my pay and go.

00:18:14.848 --> 00:18:16.338
- Bye.
- Get home safe.

00:18:16.338 --> 00:18:18.818
Thanks.

00:18:24.334 --> 00:18:27.004
Ms. Ui Yeong, do you have time tomorrow?

00:18:27.004 --> 00:18:28.500
Huh?

00:18:28.500 --> 00:18:30.700
He texted?

00:18:39.274 --> 00:18:42.307
A peck must be nice.

00:18:42.307 --> 00:18:45.900
A peck turns into a kiss,

00:18:45.900 --> 00:18:47.960
and when you kiss...

00:18:49.021 --> 00:18:53.847
It's not easy for two people
to have that kind of chemistry right away.

00:19:06.641 --> 00:19:09.860
I've got work, so I'll head out first.

00:19:18.483 --> 00:19:21.016
I've never had a Cinderella-at-night moment

00:19:21.016 --> 00:19:23.963
like that before.

00:19:24.633 --> 00:19:28.227
- Cinderella?
- No idea.

00:19:36.179 --> 00:19:37.685
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

00:19:37.685 --> 00:19:39.249
Do you have a moment?

00:19:39.249 --> 00:19:42.889
[Deukgeun Deukgeun Gym]
Seven, eight, nine, ten.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:47.308
So today is your last PT session.

00:19:47.308 --> 00:19:49.685
You can feel the difference, right?

00:19:49.685 --> 00:19:51.878
Maybe... I lost one or two kilos.

00:19:51.878 --> 00:19:55.325
It's about the same as after
one trip to the bathroom.

00:19:55.325 --> 00:19:58.321
But you've gained muscle and lost body fat.

00:19:58.321 --> 00:20:00.345
If the scale changed by one or two kilos,

00:20:00.345 --> 00:20:02.148
that's actually great progress.

00:20:02.148 --> 00:20:04.282
You've built a solid workout habit.

00:20:04.282 --> 00:20:07.512
But the money leaving my account
is very noticeable.

00:20:07.512 --> 00:20:10.523
My husband nags me nonstop, you know.

00:20:10.523 --> 00:20:12.954
Then bring your husband next time.

00:20:12.954 --> 00:20:14.458
I'll make sure he has nothing to nag about...

00:20:14.458 --> 00:20:16.716
Please, that would be a disaster.

00:20:16.716 --> 00:20:18.682
Your phone keeps going off.

00:20:18.682 --> 00:20:20.935
Oh, sorry about that.

00:20:20.935 --> 00:20:23.006
Then I'm heading out.

00:20:23.006 --> 00:20:24.761
Ma'am.

00:20:24.761 --> 00:20:27.599
Ma'am.

00:20:33.050 --> 00:20:34.187
What are you doing?

00:20:34.187 --> 00:20:36.251
You must've thought about me at least once.

00:20:36.251 --> 00:20:37.468
Want to meet today?

00:20:37.468 --> 00:20:39.727
Wait...

00:20:39.727 --> 00:20:42.366
Did I get caught?

00:21:04.375 --> 00:21:06.592
I should've just told the truth.

00:21:06.592 --> 00:21:10.064
At least I wouldn't look this bad.

00:21:10.064 --> 00:21:12.055
I'm busy today.

00:21:12.055 --> 00:21:14.221
What happened that day was a mistake.

00:21:14.221 --> 00:21:16.606
Please don't be upset.

00:21:16.606 --> 00:21:19.659
[Send money via SoonmuPay]

00:21:20.523 --> 00:21:21.947
[To HeungJeongMangJeong]

00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:25.887
[To HeungJeongMangJeong]
15,000 won...

00:21:25.887 --> 00:21:29.060
Is that too much?

00:21:29.060 --> 00:21:30.617
Then...

00:21:30.617 --> 00:21:31.977
10,000 won.

00:21:31.977 --> 00:21:33.395
[Enter your SoonmuPay password]

00:21:33.395 --> 00:21:35.913
[10,000 won sent to HeungJeongMangJeong]
Could you check this machine?

00:21:35.913 --> 00:21:37.957
Sure.

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:41.573
[10,000 won sent]
What?

00:21:42.807 --> 00:21:45.880
Is this punk seriously sending me money?

00:21:45.880 --> 00:21:48.324
What the...

00:21:48.324 --> 00:21:50.514
Does he have mayonnaise in his head
instead of a brain?

00:21:50.514 --> 00:21:52.777
You jerk!

00:21:52.777 --> 00:21:55.323
I got you now!

00:22:22.007 --> 00:22:23.950
Hello, this is Deukgeun Deukgeun Gym.

00:22:23.950 --> 00:22:27.676
Hello? Is this Mr. Lim Seung Jun?

00:22:29.302 --> 00:22:30.859
Yes, that's right.

00:22:30.859 --> 00:22:31.905
Who is this?

00:22:31.905 --> 00:22:33.719
This is the Soonmu Market operations team.

00:22:33.719 --> 00:22:35.489
You recently sold some comic books, correct?

00:22:35.489 --> 00:22:38.097
The buyer has filed a report.

00:22:38.097 --> 00:22:40.254
For inappropriate conduct
and fraud in a direct transaction.

00:22:40.254 --> 00:22:41.470
Do you admit to this?

00:22:41.470 --> 00:22:42.526
What?

00:22:42.526 --> 00:22:44.973
[Did you just send money?]
[Are you completely nuts?]

00:22:44.973 --> 00:22:48.746
[You think I'm a joke?]
[Why aren't you answering?]

00:22:50.969 --> 00:22:54.168
[Want me to break your neck?]
What is this supposed to be?

00:22:56.538 --> 00:22:57.929
- Ui Yeong.
- Yeah?

00:22:59.564 --> 00:23:03.021
Here's the tasting list and the recipes
for the whiskey pop-up.

00:23:03.021 --> 00:23:04.348
Okay.

00:23:04.348 --> 00:23:06.731
Oh, Sae Byeok.
Did you find the bartender for the event?

00:23:06.731 --> 00:23:08.121
Yes, I booked one.

00:23:08.121 --> 00:23:10.189
I'll send the profile by email.

00:23:10.189 --> 00:23:12.982
- Great.
- Alright.

00:23:14.395 --> 00:23:15.645
Dear HeungJeongMangJeong,

00:23:15.645 --> 00:23:18.452
I truly didn't mean to upset you.

00:23:18.452 --> 00:23:21.182
I'd like to apologize. Could we meet today?

00:23:21.182 --> 00:23:22.332
Oh, yeah?

00:23:22.332 --> 00:23:24.599
So you want to throw down the gauntlet?

00:23:24.599 --> 00:23:26.789
- That Soonmu Market?
- Yeah.

00:23:26.789 --> 00:23:30.639
Turns out it's not even recyclable.
Total trash!

00:23:30.639 --> 00:23:33.350
- The comic books?
- No. The seller.

00:23:33.350 --> 00:23:36.522
Looks like he skipped sex ed,
ethics class, and basic language lessons.

00:23:36.522 --> 00:23:39.828
I'm going to educate him today.

00:23:40.727 --> 00:23:42.121
[Song Tae Seop]

00:23:46.583 --> 00:23:49.430
Hello.

00:23:49.430 --> 00:23:51.723
Right now?

00:23:51.723 --> 00:23:55.270
You're coming to the office?

00:24:03.481 --> 00:24:06.721
Is this the only cafe around here?

00:24:08.067 --> 00:24:09.606
Your drinks are ready.

00:24:09.606 --> 00:24:11.537
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

00:24:11.537 --> 00:24:13.893
Thank you.

00:24:13.893 --> 00:24:15.990
Hey, do you have a girlfriend?

00:24:15.990 --> 00:24:18.296
- That's a secret.
- Come on, tell us.

00:24:18.296 --> 00:24:20.815
- She's the one who brought us all here today.
- Right.

00:24:20.815 --> 00:24:23.061
Come back three more times and I'll tell you.

00:24:23.061 --> 00:24:24.282
- Please.
- We have to come...

00:24:24.282 --> 00:24:26.428
Welcome...

00:24:27.699 --> 00:24:29.437
You're here... again?

00:24:29.437 --> 00:24:30.759
Yeah.

00:24:30.759 --> 00:24:33.776
Do the staff here pick and choose
which customers to welcome?

00:24:33.776 --> 00:24:36.281
Well, the staff are human too.

00:24:36.281 --> 00:24:38.186
Some customers are less welcome than others.

00:24:38.186 --> 00:24:40.033
Yeah?

00:24:40.033 --> 00:24:44.339
Four iced Americanos. To go.

00:24:46.453 --> 00:24:49.187
About last time, I ended up lying to you.

00:24:49.187 --> 00:24:52.497
You know I'm not her cousin, right?

00:24:52.497 --> 00:24:55.990
Yeah, it doesn't matter.

00:24:57.920 --> 00:24:59.331
Get the chocolate one.

00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:00.877
Ui Yeong loves chocolate.

00:25:00.877 --> 00:25:03.802
Then I'll take the carrot cake

00:25:03.802 --> 00:25:07.110
next to the chocolate one.

00:25:07.110 --> 00:25:09.254
There are a lot of people at her office.

00:25:09.254 --> 00:25:12.430
The chocolate one's on me.

00:25:12.430 --> 00:25:15.761
The cake's just for the two of us.

00:25:15.761 --> 00:25:18.654
Thanks for the freebie.

00:25:39.127 --> 00:25:40.584
Excuse me.

00:25:40.584 --> 00:25:43.378
- Oh, Mr. Song.
- Hello.

00:25:43.378 --> 00:25:45.642
You even brought cake.

00:25:45.642 --> 00:25:48.695
- Oh, thank you.
- Thanks.

00:25:50.137 --> 00:25:52.162
Shall we head upstairs?

00:25:52.162 --> 00:25:54.055
Okay.

00:25:54.055 --> 00:25:55.904
- I'll be back.
- Yeah.

00:25:55.904 --> 00:25:58.430
See you later.

00:26:39.542 --> 00:26:42.296
Is something wrong?

00:26:42.296 --> 00:26:44.776
There's something I'm stuck on.

00:26:44.776 --> 00:26:47.853
I thought talking it through with you
might help me sort it out.

00:26:47.853 --> 00:26:50.566
Okay, what is it?

00:26:52.153 --> 00:26:54.477
There's not much space we can really use here.

00:26:54.477 --> 00:26:56.750
Yeah. We've tried a few designs,

00:26:56.750 --> 00:26:59.970
but none of them really fit the room.

00:26:59.970 --> 00:27:01.754
What could we do...

00:27:01.754 --> 00:27:05.330
Let me run a little simulation.

00:27:06.707 --> 00:27:09.959
First I check in, come into the room,

00:27:09.959 --> 00:27:11.896
look around,

00:27:11.896 --> 00:27:13.563
and take photos.

00:27:13.563 --> 00:27:15.067
Maybe a selfie too.

00:27:15.067 --> 00:27:16.910
And then...

00:27:16.910 --> 00:27:19.032
I immediately

00:27:19.032 --> 00:27:21.983
- lie down.
- Oh.

00:27:21.983 --> 00:27:27.081
I roll around, lie this way, and that way.

00:27:27.081 --> 00:27:28.681
Basically I become one with the bed.

00:27:28.681 --> 00:27:31.087
- Maybe watch some TV.
- I see.

00:27:31.087 --> 00:27:32.472
So you're that type.

00:27:32.472 --> 00:27:35.663
And the only time I finally get up

00:27:35.663 --> 00:27:38.263
is when I'm hungry.

00:27:40.030 --> 00:27:41.247
Mr. Tae Seop,

00:27:41.247 --> 00:27:43.001
what if we did something on the bed?

00:27:43.001 --> 00:27:44.505
- On the bed?
- Yeah.

00:27:44.505 --> 00:27:45.815
Like those trays.

00:27:45.815 --> 00:27:48.705
People use them while sitting in bed.

00:27:56.028 --> 00:27:58.715
- A soban.
- A soban?

00:27:58.715 --> 00:28:01.106
When I was little,
I'd set one up on the bedding.

00:28:01.106 --> 00:28:04.179
I'd eat there or draw on it.

00:28:05.514 --> 00:28:07.297
That actually sounds nice.

00:28:07.297 --> 00:28:09.105
It wouldn't take up much space,

00:28:09.105 --> 00:28:10.830
and surprisingly,
it might go well with whiskey.

00:28:10.830 --> 00:28:12.664
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:28:12.664 --> 00:28:13.801
Then,

00:28:13.801 --> 00:28:16.854
the bedding should probably be a darker color.

00:28:16.854 --> 00:28:20.033
So spills won't stand out.

00:28:22.146 --> 00:28:24.090
Let's go with the soban as the main item

00:28:24.090 --> 00:28:25.688
and design around it.

00:28:25.688 --> 00:28:26.715
High five?

00:28:26.715 --> 00:28:29.381
- Yeah!
- Oh...

00:28:47.954 --> 00:28:50.546
Ms. Ui Yeong?

00:28:53.298 --> 00:28:55.771
She's not here?

00:28:56.604 --> 00:28:58.575
She said she was looking around the rooms.

00:28:58.575 --> 00:29:00.948
Where did she go?

00:29:01.543 --> 00:29:04.377
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:29:05.491 --> 00:29:08.230
Did she go to another room?

00:29:33.461 --> 00:29:35.896
It's almost time for you
to get off work, right?

00:29:35.896 --> 00:29:36.986
Yes.

00:29:36.986 --> 00:29:39.672
I'll give you a ride home.

00:29:49.936 --> 00:29:50.972
[Seasons of Us]

00:29:50.972 --> 00:29:52.962
Looks like
"Seasons of Us" is being re-released.

00:29:52.962 --> 00:29:54.650
"Seasons of Us?"

00:29:54.650 --> 00:29:56.976
Is it good?

00:29:56.976 --> 00:29:58.120
You haven't seen it?

00:29:58.120 --> 00:30:00.253
That movie hit ten million viewers.

00:30:00.253 --> 00:30:03.319
I like that actress,
so I've seen it three times.

00:30:03.319 --> 00:30:05.043
Oh, really?

00:30:05.043 --> 00:30:06.780
Then I should definitely watch it.

00:30:06.780 --> 00:30:08.406
- Mr. Tae Seop.
- Yeah?

00:30:08.406 --> 00:30:10.390
We came up with the idea today,

00:30:10.390 --> 00:30:12.514
and once the pop-up installation is done,

00:30:12.514 --> 00:30:15.262
the important part is basically over, right?

00:30:15.262 --> 00:30:16.673
Yeah, pretty much.

00:30:16.673 --> 00:30:19.363
Then after we finish work that day,

00:30:19.363 --> 00:30:22.183
want to go see the late-night showing?

00:30:22.183 --> 00:30:24.281
That movie is really good.

00:30:24.281 --> 00:30:27.893
It'd be a shame to miss it.

00:30:27.893 --> 00:30:29.177
Sounds good.

00:30:29.177 --> 00:30:31.064
Let's grab something good to eat too.

00:30:31.064 --> 00:30:32.334
What do you like?

00:30:32.334 --> 00:30:33.859
Me?

00:30:33.859 --> 00:30:37.259
I'm not picky at all.
I eat pretty much anything.

00:30:38.386 --> 00:30:40.700
I can't wait.

00:30:49.749 --> 00:30:52.252
Did you just get off work?

00:30:52.252 --> 00:30:54.637
- Must've been a long day.
- Enough.

00:30:54.637 --> 00:30:56.901
This is your last chance.
Choose your words carefully.

00:30:56.901 --> 00:30:59.878
I'm really sorry for
not understanding how you felt.

00:30:59.878 --> 00:31:03.371
I'm not very experienced
with this kind of thing.

00:31:07.272 --> 00:31:09.458
Will this work?

00:31:16.308 --> 00:31:19.185
This punk...

00:31:19.185 --> 00:31:24.317
Didn't I say this was your last chance?

00:31:24.317 --> 00:31:26.255
Didn't I say this was

00:31:26.255 --> 00:31:27.861
- your last chance?
- Hey, calm down.

00:31:27.861 --> 00:31:29.635
- Let's talk this out.
- Are you an idiot?

00:31:29.635 --> 00:31:31.740
It's not even that expensive!

00:31:31.740 --> 00:31:33.698
What?

00:31:33.698 --> 00:31:38.445
Who do you think you are,
deciding what's expensive or not for me?

00:31:41.954 --> 00:31:43.612
Wait a second.

00:31:43.612 --> 00:31:46.518
When did I put a price on anything?

00:31:49.893 --> 00:31:53.920
I never imagined that was the price of...

00:31:53.920 --> 00:31:56.010
a ripped comic book.

00:31:56.010 --> 00:31:59.136
What kind of person do you think I am?

00:32:01.456 --> 00:32:04.796
I'm a trainer. I don't eat fried food.

00:32:04.796 --> 00:32:06.366
I worked hard for this body.

00:32:06.366 --> 00:32:08.800
Yeah, you should protect those nice muscles.

00:32:08.800 --> 00:32:10.778
I'm Jung Hyun Min, thirty years old.

00:32:10.778 --> 00:32:12.017
I work at a company.

00:32:12.017 --> 00:32:13.767
But I've been wondering...

00:32:13.767 --> 00:32:16.603
Why did you clean my place
before you left that day?

00:32:26.737 --> 00:32:28.368
Well...

00:32:28.368 --> 00:32:31.581
If only the books were put away,
that'd look suspicious.

00:32:57.169 --> 00:32:58.486
I mean...

00:32:58.486 --> 00:33:01.040
if I'd just taken the comics and left,
that would've looked weird.

00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:04.320
So I just cleaned up while I was at it.

00:33:21.678 --> 00:33:23.536
So you can eat this, right?

00:33:23.536 --> 00:33:28.309
I'm pretty good at peeling things, by the way.

00:33:49.985 --> 00:33:51.163
By the way,

00:33:51.163 --> 00:33:54.905
once you sleep with someone,
do you lose interest in them?

00:33:57.303 --> 00:33:59.327
No, not at all.

00:33:59.327 --> 00:34:01.140
Lower your voice.

00:34:01.140 --> 00:34:03.037
Oh, thank goodness.

00:34:03.037 --> 00:34:05.661
Because I really like you.

00:34:05.661 --> 00:34:08.121
What do you think of me?

00:34:08.121 --> 00:34:10.611
In this situation, you're really asking that?

00:34:10.611 --> 00:34:12.835
Yeah, the misunderstanding's cleared up.

00:34:12.835 --> 00:34:14.512
Your bruise will heal soon.

00:34:14.512 --> 00:34:17.142
We can even eat this whole chicken
without fighting.

00:34:17.142 --> 00:34:20.515
Everything feels pretty great right now.

00:34:20.515 --> 00:34:23.795
So... why don't we get to know each other?

00:34:45.230 --> 00:34:46.367
Mr. Tae Seop,

00:34:46.367 --> 00:34:49.873
you're coming
for the pop-up installation today, right?

00:34:52.285 --> 00:34:55.245
Yes, see you soon.

00:34:55.995 --> 00:34:57.312
Hey, watch the back.

00:34:57.312 --> 00:34:59.305
Be careful.

00:34:59.305 --> 00:35:02.632
You're going to break everything.

00:35:03.722 --> 00:35:06.861
A white shirt on installation day?

00:35:06.861 --> 00:35:08.893
- Oh, good timing.
- What?

00:35:08.893 --> 00:35:11.679
You know that professor in Hannam-dong
who bought the desk from us?

00:35:11.679 --> 00:35:14.858
He called asking if we could move the meeting
to tonight.

00:35:14.858 --> 00:35:16.569
But I have to take Sua to the hospital,

00:35:16.569 --> 00:35:18.158
- so can you handle it?
- What?

00:35:18.158 --> 00:35:19.839
I can't, I have to go to the hotel.

00:35:19.839 --> 00:35:21.553
He's a regular. Let's do him a favor.

00:35:21.553 --> 00:35:23.263
He says it's because of
his kid's academy schedule.

00:35:23.263 --> 00:35:26.184
You can head over after the meeting.

00:35:27.304 --> 00:35:29.892
Then tell him to come as early as possible.

00:35:29.892 --> 00:35:31.978
Jin Su!

00:35:33.106 --> 00:35:34.163
Yes?

00:35:34.163 --> 00:35:36.290
I'll head over after the meeting,
so let them know,

00:35:36.290 --> 00:35:38.007
and send me some photos
during the installation.

00:35:38.007 --> 00:35:39.140
- Oh, photos?
- Yeah.

00:35:39.140 --> 00:35:41.060
Got it.

00:35:42.346 --> 00:35:44.970
That intern reminds me of Senior Ui Yeong.

00:35:44.970 --> 00:35:46.560
Acts all innocent, but she's sly.

00:35:46.560 --> 00:35:51.111
Looks kind,
but she's actually hard to deal with.

00:35:51.111 --> 00:35:53.468
You've changed your salary, your car,

00:35:53.468 --> 00:35:55.638
even your taste in liquor.

00:35:55.638 --> 00:35:58.288
So why is your taste in women still the same?

00:35:58.288 --> 00:36:00.508
Yeah?

00:36:00.508 --> 00:36:03.538
Stop chasing a lost cause.

00:36:03.538 --> 00:36:05.435
There are plenty of girls
who'd say yes if I introduced you.

00:36:05.435 --> 00:36:08.454
You really have no plans
to go back to the firm?

00:36:20.888 --> 00:36:21.918
Okay.

00:36:21.918 --> 00:36:25.447
Alright, let's go. One, two, three.

00:36:31.262 --> 00:36:32.892
- Hello.
- Oh, hi.

00:36:32.892 --> 00:36:34.706
Is the CEO not coming?

00:36:34.706 --> 00:36:37.157
He couldn't make it
because of a client meeting.

00:36:37.157 --> 00:36:38.858
Didn't he let you know?

00:36:38.858 --> 00:36:41.674
I didn't...

00:36:41.674 --> 00:36:42.716
get a message.

00:36:42.716 --> 00:36:45.549
He must've forgotten. It happens a lot.

00:36:45.549 --> 00:36:47.602
I see.

00:36:49.549 --> 00:36:52.026
Excuse me,
which floor should we take all this to?

00:36:52.026 --> 00:36:54.026
Please move everything to the L floor.

00:36:54.026 --> 00:36:56.352
This way, please.

00:36:59.925 --> 00:37:02.270
Watch your step.

00:37:02.270 --> 00:37:04.278
Take it slow.

00:37:06.368 --> 00:37:08.814
Over there? Okay.

00:37:12.831 --> 00:37:15.184
You didn't have to move all of it.

00:37:15.184 --> 00:37:17.612
I think I grabbed too much.

00:37:17.612 --> 00:37:19.183
- Let me hold that for you.
- Thank you.

00:37:19.183 --> 00:37:21.022
This is pretty heavy.

00:37:21.022 --> 00:37:22.720
Yeah.

00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:24.800
This way.

00:37:24.800 --> 00:37:28.213
She sure has no problem
accepting help from others.

00:37:28.213 --> 00:37:29.997
See you tomorrow at six.

00:37:29.997 --> 00:37:31.870
Okay.

00:37:34.449 --> 00:37:36.840
- Welcome.
- Hello.

00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:39.614
- Are you ready to order?
- Yeah.

00:37:39.614 --> 00:37:42.757
Ten hot Americanos,

00:37:42.757 --> 00:37:45.067
ten iced ones,

00:37:45.067 --> 00:37:48.720
and this hot chocolate here.

00:37:48.720 --> 00:37:50.734
And I'll take all of these.

00:37:50.734 --> 00:37:52.091
All of them?

00:37:52.091 --> 00:37:53.217
Yes.

00:37:53.217 --> 00:37:55.437
Ji Su...

00:38:02.969 --> 00:38:06.309
- Come again.
- Thanks.

00:38:10.796 --> 00:38:12.470
Excuse me.

00:38:12.470 --> 00:38:14.039
Is the place you're going nearby?

00:38:14.039 --> 00:38:15.712
Well...

00:38:15.712 --> 00:38:16.915
The Hills Hotel.

00:38:16.915 --> 00:38:19.514
Someone I like is working late there.

00:38:20.485 --> 00:38:22.712
A hotel?

00:38:33.826 --> 00:38:35.697
Here, just leave it here.

00:38:35.697 --> 00:38:38.139
- Oh, okay.
- Yeah.

00:38:38.139 --> 00:38:40.360
Alright then.

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:42.832
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

00:38:46.737 --> 00:38:48.434
What are you doing here?

00:38:48.434 --> 00:38:49.799
Delivery.

00:38:49.799 --> 00:38:51.079
You deliver now?

00:38:51.079 --> 00:38:52.821
Just today.

00:38:52.821 --> 00:38:54.071
- Working late?
- Yeah...

00:38:54.071 --> 00:38:55.414
I've got that event I told you about.

00:38:55.414 --> 00:38:58.229
Everyone, help yourselves to some coffee.

00:38:58.229 --> 00:39:00.173
- Kang Do Hyun?
- Have some coffee.

00:39:00.173 --> 00:39:02.689
Sae Byeok! Over here.

00:39:02.689 --> 00:39:04.486
Attorney Kang,

00:39:04.486 --> 00:39:06.832
what are you doing here?

00:39:06.832 --> 00:39:08.130
Well...

00:39:08.130 --> 00:39:11.090
It looked like you were working late,
so I brought some coffee.

00:39:11.090 --> 00:39:13.734
Since it's late, I got you hot chocolate.

00:39:13.734 --> 00:39:15.858
Hold on, I'll find it.

00:39:15.858 --> 00:39:18.395
- Just a moment.
- I'm really fine.

00:39:18.395 --> 00:39:22.234
Why didn't he mark this?

00:39:23.795 --> 00:39:26.876
Hey, Attorney Kang.

00:39:26.876 --> 00:39:29.445
Did I ever ask for this?

00:39:29.445 --> 00:39:31.070
No, right?

00:39:31.070 --> 00:39:33.336
Hold on a second.

00:39:35.484 --> 00:39:37.310
Kang Do Hyun,

00:39:37.310 --> 00:39:38.427
you can talk tomorrow.

00:39:38.427 --> 00:39:40.480
There are people from other companies here.

00:39:40.480 --> 00:39:43.698
Come on, it's just coffee.
What's wrong with buying coffee?

00:39:43.698 --> 00:39:47.021
If the person receiving it feels uncomfortable,

00:39:47.021 --> 00:39:48.765
you should think about that too.

00:39:48.765 --> 00:39:51.155
You're partly responsible
for this situation too.

00:39:51.155 --> 00:39:52.210
What?

00:39:52.210 --> 00:39:54.995
You don't even feel sorry toward me?

00:39:54.995 --> 00:39:57.242
For what?

00:39:57.242 --> 00:39:58.729
You know...

00:39:58.729 --> 00:40:01.372
Ui Yeong, because of you,

00:40:01.372 --> 00:40:05.175
Sae Byeok feels uncomfortable around me.

00:40:05.175 --> 00:40:07.241
Why...

00:40:08.268 --> 00:40:12.756
Why are you acting like you like me now?

00:40:12.756 --> 00:40:15.096
Just to get in the way of my love...

00:40:15.096 --> 00:40:17.342
What?

00:40:17.342 --> 00:40:19.675
Well...

00:40:25.793 --> 00:40:28.040
I'm leaving.

00:40:28.040 --> 00:40:31.713
I'll take all of this with me.

00:40:32.900 --> 00:40:35.440
Oh, be careful!

00:40:37.187 --> 00:40:39.460
Oh my!

00:40:40.747 --> 00:40:42.853
Hey, are you okay?

00:40:42.853 --> 00:40:45.627
- It's hot...
- Let's go to the hospital.

00:40:48.477 --> 00:40:50.469
Get something to wipe this up!

00:40:50.469 --> 00:40:52.749
Oh gosh...

00:40:54.763 --> 00:40:57.364
Attorney Kang,

00:40:57.364 --> 00:41:00.995
I think you're seriously mistaken
about something.

00:41:00.995 --> 00:41:02.866
It's not because of her.

00:41:02.866 --> 00:41:05.162
It's just that... people like you,

00:41:05.162 --> 00:41:08.760
who make such a big deal out of
their own feelings,

00:41:08.760 --> 00:41:13.330
make me uncomfortable.

00:41:13.330 --> 00:41:14.901
Yeah...

00:41:14.901 --> 00:41:16.085
I actually hate that.

00:41:16.085 --> 00:41:17.969
Not as a friend, not as a coworker.

00:41:17.969 --> 00:41:21.162
So please...

00:41:21.162 --> 00:41:24.002
don't like me.

00:41:29.527 --> 00:41:32.593
Hey, get this one first.

00:41:39.803 --> 00:41:41.517
Hey, Jin Su.

00:41:41.517 --> 00:41:44.001
- Call the boss.
- Yeah, okay.

00:41:44.001 --> 00:41:47.432
[Under Construction]

00:41:51.776 --> 00:41:55.532
Sorry, I'm a bit late. Something came up,
so I'm heading out now.

00:41:59.826 --> 00:42:02.479
[Jin Su]
[Sir, we've got a problem.]

00:42:07.605 --> 00:42:09.629
Sir, we've got a problem.

00:42:09.629 --> 00:42:12.572
You should come take a look.

00:42:12.572 --> 00:42:14.838
Why is this...

00:42:17.219 --> 00:42:19.243
Fortunately, it's nothing serious.

00:42:19.243 --> 00:42:22.085
Thank you.

00:42:26.278 --> 00:42:29.078
- Here's your receipt.
- Thank you.

00:42:43.741 --> 00:42:47.148
You should've been careful
with even a single drop.

00:42:47.148 --> 00:42:49.379
I'm sorry. It was my mistake.

00:42:49.379 --> 00:42:52.403
Everyone else worked hard the whole time.

00:42:52.403 --> 00:42:54.240
No, it wasn't your fault.

00:42:54.240 --> 00:42:57.216
Something unexpected happened.

00:42:57.216 --> 00:42:59.665
Let's finish it again with a darker oil.

00:42:59.665 --> 00:43:00.882
All of the furniture?

00:43:00.882 --> 00:43:02.455
If we want the colors to match, we have to.

00:43:02.455 --> 00:43:04.180
Let's hurry and finish today.

00:43:04.180 --> 00:43:06.095
Yes.

00:43:34.703 --> 00:43:38.382
You have to spread it like this.

00:43:38.382 --> 00:43:41.163
[Emergency Medical Center]

00:43:41.163 --> 00:43:42.665
Well...

00:43:42.665 --> 00:43:45.502
I think I should head back to the hotel.

00:43:45.502 --> 00:43:48.341
You're going back to the hotel
in that condition?

00:43:48.341 --> 00:43:51.206
I rushed out, so I think I dropped my phone.

00:43:51.206 --> 00:43:53.510
And they must be in chaos
trying to fix the furniture.

00:43:53.510 --> 00:43:56.272
I should go check.

00:44:00.206 --> 00:44:02.657
Call them first.

00:44:02.657 --> 00:44:04.779
Okay.

00:44:11.659 --> 00:44:14.439
Where should I move this?

00:44:15.793 --> 00:44:19.531
CEO Song came and is helping fix things.

00:44:19.531 --> 00:44:21.272
Oh, he's there?

00:44:21.272 --> 00:44:23.092
We're almost done anyway,

00:44:23.092 --> 00:44:25.368
just get some rest at home.

00:44:25.368 --> 00:44:26.545
You were hurt, right?

00:44:26.545 --> 00:44:28.338
I'm really sorry.

00:44:28.338 --> 00:44:31.715
Hey, why are you apologizing?

00:44:31.715 --> 00:44:34.192
Alright then. I'll head home today.

00:44:34.192 --> 00:44:36.489
- See you tomorrow.
- Yeah, see you tomorrow.

00:44:36.489 --> 00:44:38.691
Okay.

00:44:40.664 --> 00:44:42.997
Let's just go home.

00:44:42.997 --> 00:44:46.455
Before we go, let's stop by one place.

00:44:46.455 --> 00:44:49.559
Oh, I meant to ask earlier
but things were hectic.

00:44:49.559 --> 00:44:51.176
Why are there two helmets?

00:44:51.176 --> 00:44:52.523
One for me, one for you.

00:44:52.523 --> 00:44:55.896
You said you wanted to try riding a motorcycle.

00:45:11.643 --> 00:45:13.366
This feels so good.

00:45:13.366 --> 00:45:14.653
What?

00:45:14.653 --> 00:45:17.453
I said it feels great!

00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:21.773
It feels like a huge weight
just lifted off my chest.

00:45:31.787 --> 00:45:34.117
When Ms. Ui Yeong stepped in to stop him,

00:45:34.117 --> 00:45:36.508
that guy started complaining
right in front of everyone.

00:45:36.508 --> 00:45:38.585
Saying things would've been fine
if she wasn't there.

00:45:38.585 --> 00:45:40.980
What else could that mean?

00:45:40.980 --> 00:45:42.724
A love triangle.

00:45:42.724 --> 00:45:44.423
That can't be.

00:45:44.423 --> 00:45:45.468
Come on.

00:45:45.468 --> 00:45:47.640
Attorney Kang likes Ms. Sae Byeok.

00:45:47.640 --> 00:45:48.888
If Ms. Ui Yeong's getting in the way,

00:45:48.888 --> 00:45:51.404
then either they're dating
or at least something's going on.

00:45:51.404 --> 00:45:53.876
You've never even dated. What would you know?

00:45:53.876 --> 00:45:56.904
Even so, they don't match.

00:45:56.904 --> 00:45:58.349
Look.

00:45:58.349 --> 00:46:01.149
That's the lawyer from earlier.

00:46:16.537 --> 00:46:19.020
Mr. Song Tae Seop?

00:46:19.020 --> 00:46:21.025
Attorney Kang,

00:46:21.025 --> 00:46:24.171
can we talk for a moment?

00:46:25.793 --> 00:46:28.293
About what?

00:46:29.434 --> 00:46:32.498
If this is about the furniture,
I had unavoidable circumstances...

00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:35.291
That made me angry too, but we're handling it.

00:46:35.291 --> 00:46:37.995
If it comes down to it,
I could hold you liable for breach of contract.

00:46:37.995 --> 00:46:40.699
The responsible party is obvious.

00:46:40.699 --> 00:46:44.775
You wrote the contract yourself,
so you know what it says.

00:46:44.775 --> 00:46:46.799
Are you threatening me right now?

00:46:46.799 --> 00:46:49.458
Threats fall under Article 283
of the criminal code...

00:46:49.458 --> 00:46:50.888
I'm not sure

00:46:50.888 --> 00:46:53.468
if this counts as a threat,

00:46:53.468 --> 00:46:56.368
but I like Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:46:56.368 --> 00:46:59.219
- What did you say?
- She's important to me.

00:46:59.219 --> 00:47:02.019
So be careful from now on.

00:47:03.711 --> 00:47:04.837
So...

00:47:04.837 --> 00:47:05.990
this is all because of her?

00:47:05.990 --> 00:47:08.733
Your words, your actions, even your thoughts.

00:47:08.733 --> 00:47:11.533
Watch them.

00:47:32.893 --> 00:47:36.159
[Sorry, I'm a bit late. Something came up...]

00:47:50.008 --> 00:47:52.535
[Song Tae Seop]

00:47:57.679 --> 00:48:00.479
[Song Tae Seop]
[Ms. Ui Yeong]

00:48:13.777 --> 00:48:15.947
What is this?

00:48:15.947 --> 00:48:18.167
Isn't this just instant ramen?

00:48:18.167 --> 00:48:19.744
Why is it so good?

00:48:19.744 --> 00:48:21.904
Because the setting isn't ordinary.

00:48:21.904 --> 00:48:25.557
It feels like it's soothing your soul, right?

00:48:33.955 --> 00:48:36.361
I'm full.

00:48:37.095 --> 00:48:41.921
By the way, did you like that lawyer too?

00:48:41.921 --> 00:48:43.185
Do you fall for guys that fast?

00:48:43.185 --> 00:48:44.899
Hey, no.

00:48:44.899 --> 00:48:46.649
That guy was just...

00:48:46.649 --> 00:48:48.109
a passing thing.

00:48:48.109 --> 00:48:50.929
Your taste in men is really...

00:48:50.929 --> 00:48:53.514
And don't trust that guy you kissed too much.

00:48:53.514 --> 00:48:57.093
All this chaos today
and he didn't even show up.

00:48:57.093 --> 00:49:00.446
He's the boss. He must be busy.

00:49:00.446 --> 00:49:02.823
But you must be tired too.

00:49:02.823 --> 00:49:04.847
You said you worked today, right?

00:49:04.847 --> 00:49:07.037
Is the cafe job hard?

00:49:07.037 --> 00:49:11.253
If you did more movies or dramas,
you'd probably make better money.

00:49:11.253 --> 00:49:13.917
I don't act to make money.

00:49:13.917 --> 00:49:15.197
I just do it because I like it.

00:49:15.197 --> 00:49:18.534
Still, if you love acting,
why not make money from it too?

00:49:18.534 --> 00:49:20.501
And it wouldn't hurt to become famous.

00:49:20.501 --> 00:49:21.959
There'd be a price for that.

00:49:21.959 --> 00:49:25.819
Like giving up moments like this.

00:49:26.854 --> 00:49:28.806
To me, this view is

00:49:28.806 --> 00:49:31.681
more comforting

00:49:32.287 --> 00:49:35.187
than money or fame.

00:49:44.769 --> 00:49:46.472
Thank you.

00:49:46.472 --> 00:49:48.256
- Have this.
- Thanks.

00:49:48.256 --> 00:49:49.962
You worked hard today, staying this late.

00:49:49.962 --> 00:49:51.265
No, not at all.

00:49:51.265 --> 00:49:54.730
Thank you so much for helping us.

00:49:56.116 --> 00:49:59.830
Did you want to say something?

00:49:59.830 --> 00:50:00.927
Nothing.

00:50:00.927 --> 00:50:04.133
Your arms and shoulders might feel sore,
so put on a patch before bed.

00:50:04.133 --> 00:50:06.283
Okay. Thank you for today.

00:50:06.283 --> 00:50:08.823
- You too.
- Yeah.

00:50:45.309 --> 00:50:47.066
They say sadness dissolves in water.

00:50:47.066 --> 00:50:48.713
Does anger evaporate?

00:50:48.713 --> 00:50:50.435
The wind just blew it all away.

00:50:50.435 --> 00:50:52.276
Let me know if you want to go for another ride.

00:50:52.276 --> 00:50:55.150
And at night, I make drinks at the cafe too.

00:50:55.150 --> 00:50:57.847
Come by sometime. I'll take good care of you.

00:50:57.847 --> 00:51:00.773
Here, my number.

00:51:16.403 --> 00:51:18.753
Mr. Tae Seop? What are you doing here?

00:51:18.753 --> 00:51:20.960
You left your phone.

00:51:20.960 --> 00:51:23.381
Oh, I thought
I'd have to come back for it tomorrow.

00:51:23.381 --> 00:51:24.418
Thank you.

00:51:24.418 --> 00:51:28.963
Can we talk for a moment? It won't take long.

00:51:28.963 --> 00:51:31.114
I'll talk to him for a bit.

00:51:31.114 --> 00:51:32.221
You go ahead.

00:51:32.221 --> 00:51:35.160
- Thanks for today.
- Alright.

00:51:37.810 --> 00:51:39.527
What happened to your arm?

00:51:39.527 --> 00:51:41.784
Did you go to the hospital?

00:51:41.784 --> 00:51:43.708
I got burned by some coffee,

00:51:43.708 --> 00:51:46.331
but they said it's nothing serious.

00:51:46.331 --> 00:51:50.468
I heard from Sae Byeok
that you handled things at the site.

00:51:50.468 --> 00:51:51.678
Thank you.

00:51:51.678 --> 00:51:53.342
If I'd gotten there a little sooner,

00:51:53.342 --> 00:51:55.723
it probably wouldn't have gotten this bad.

00:51:55.723 --> 00:51:59.222
You had something to deal with, that's all.

00:52:00.200 --> 00:52:02.694
But honestly...

00:52:02.694 --> 00:52:07.027
I did wait for you.

00:52:07.753 --> 00:52:09.291
I'm sorry.

00:52:09.291 --> 00:52:11.942
From now on, I won't be late

00:52:11.942 --> 00:52:14.950
or keep you waiting.

00:52:17.507 --> 00:52:21.484
Do you have any photos from the site?

00:52:21.484 --> 00:52:24.731
- Want to see?
- Yes.

00:52:24.731 --> 00:52:26.337
Here.

00:52:28.084 --> 00:52:30.728
It's even better than I imagined.

00:52:30.728 --> 00:52:32.941
Not bad, right?

00:52:41.902 --> 00:52:43.860
I got home safely.

00:52:43.860 --> 00:52:46.660
Get some good rest tonight.

00:52:54.755 --> 00:52:55.845
- Hyun Min,
- Yes?

00:52:55.845 --> 00:52:58.949
- everything's ready, right?
- I think we're all set.

00:52:58.949 --> 00:53:00.241
- Ms. Ui Yeong.
- Yes?

00:53:00.241 --> 00:53:02.959
The bartender we booked just called.

00:53:02.959 --> 00:53:04.876
He can't make it.
Someone in his family is sick.

00:53:04.876 --> 00:53:07.052
- What?
- On the day of the event?

00:53:07.052 --> 00:53:08.190
Yes.

00:53:08.190 --> 00:53:10.574
But we really need a bartender.

00:53:10.574 --> 00:53:13.151
What do we do?

00:53:13.151 --> 00:53:16.077
Guys, give me a second.

00:53:16.676 --> 00:53:20.692
The props you made fit our hotel perfectly.

00:53:20.692 --> 00:53:25.185
I especially love this octagonal soban.

00:53:25.185 --> 00:53:27.069
I heard the soban and bedding idea

00:53:27.069 --> 00:53:29.955
was something you and Ms. Ui Yeong
came up with together.

00:53:29.955 --> 00:53:32.605
You two have great chemistry.

00:53:32.605 --> 00:53:34.312
Thank you.

00:53:34.312 --> 00:53:35.709
And the guest rooms

00:53:35.709 --> 00:53:39.902
will first be used as a trial
by brand representatives and VIP guests.

00:53:39.902 --> 00:53:43.686
After that, we'll reorganize them
and open them to regular guests.

00:53:43.686 --> 00:53:46.750
Orders placed through the pop-up
will be collected

00:53:46.750 --> 00:53:48.416
and passed along through Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:53:48.416 --> 00:53:52.230
- Thank you. We appreciate it.
- Thank you.

00:53:52.230 --> 00:53:54.093
And this is...

00:53:54.093 --> 00:53:57.348
a small gift for the staff who worked so hard.

00:53:57.348 --> 00:53:59.173
- Oh.
- Wow.

00:53:59.173 --> 00:54:01.700
- The team is going to love this.
- Right.

00:54:01.700 --> 00:54:03.418
You can use this room.

00:54:03.418 --> 00:54:05.388
We'll call you when the pop-up opens.

00:54:05.388 --> 00:54:07.153
- Please get some rest first.
- Okay.

00:54:07.153 --> 00:54:10.032
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:54:17.584 --> 00:54:20.295
We were in a hurry,
so I just had him wear one of our uniforms.

00:54:20.295 --> 00:54:22.625
Yeah, it couldn't be helped.

00:54:22.625 --> 00:54:25.231
We did our best.

00:54:28.353 --> 00:54:30.706
How do I look?

00:54:30.706 --> 00:54:33.779
- Is it too short?
- Wow.

00:54:53.731 --> 00:54:57.116
The bartender experience booth
is very popular right now.

00:54:57.116 --> 00:54:58.936
It's great.

00:54:59.560 --> 00:55:02.513
If you purchase any two items...

00:55:15.671 --> 00:55:18.471
Here you go.

00:55:31.357 --> 00:55:33.303
Hey.

00:55:35.625 --> 00:55:37.170
My wrist is about to fall off.

00:55:37.170 --> 00:55:39.396
I said I'd make you a drink,

00:55:39.396 --> 00:55:42.053
not serve all these people.

00:55:42.053 --> 00:55:43.457
I'll make it up to you.

00:55:43.457 --> 00:55:44.657
But seriously,

00:55:44.657 --> 00:55:47.268
did this place really get designed
by that guy, Song Tae Seop?

00:55:47.268 --> 00:55:49.908
Yeah. Isn't it amazing?

00:55:51.047 --> 00:55:52.989
Oh, Mr. Tae Seop!

00:55:52.989 --> 00:55:55.377
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:55:56.098 --> 00:55:57.348
Can I get you something?

00:55:57.348 --> 00:55:58.886
No, I'm good.

00:55:58.886 --> 00:56:01.666
- Did you look around?
- Yes, it's incredible.

00:56:01.666 --> 00:56:05.016
And it seems like
the brand representatives are really pleased.

00:56:05.016 --> 00:56:06.733
That's a relief.

00:56:06.733 --> 00:56:08.173
If you have a moment...

00:56:08.173 --> 00:56:09.237
Sir,

00:56:09.237 --> 00:56:10.588
could you greet the guests over there too?

00:56:10.588 --> 00:56:11.930
Oh, yes.

00:56:11.930 --> 00:56:14.116
Just a second.

00:56:17.816 --> 00:56:20.294
Son Jeong A!

00:56:20.294 --> 00:56:22.092
What's with her?

00:56:22.092 --> 00:56:26.191
This brand has been the main sponsor
of the Geumsang Arts Awards for years.

00:56:26.191 --> 00:56:29.008
She's just beautiful.

00:56:29.008 --> 00:56:30.957
I'm a huge fan of hers.

00:56:30.957 --> 00:56:34.169
She doesn't even act anymore.

00:56:34.169 --> 00:56:37.489
She's just a celebrity now.

00:56:37.489 --> 00:56:41.149
Oh gosh, did you see that? She winked at me!

00:56:42.540 --> 00:56:45.787
You saw that, right? She winked at me.

00:57:18.832 --> 00:57:20.770
- There you are.
- Oh, hi.

00:57:20.770 --> 00:57:24.000
You looked pretty busy greeting everyone.

00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:25.150
Yeah...

00:57:25.150 --> 00:57:26.998
But things have settled down now.

00:57:26.998 --> 00:57:28.027
I know.

00:57:28.027 --> 00:57:31.446
Thanks to you,
everything seems to have gone well.

00:58:01.221 --> 00:58:02.905
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:58:02.905 --> 00:58:03.951
Yes?

00:58:03.951 --> 00:58:05.975
About that thing
we didn't get to do last time...

00:58:05.975 --> 00:58:07.599
- Ms. Ui Yeong!
- Yes?

00:58:07.599 --> 00:58:10.643
Some people didn't seem to know
about the after-party tonight.

00:58:10.643 --> 00:58:12.393
You did send the notice, right?

00:58:12.393 --> 00:58:13.427
Oh, right.

00:58:13.427 --> 00:58:16.066
Geez...

00:58:16.066 --> 00:58:17.816
You're coming too, right?

00:58:17.816 --> 00:58:19.504
I actually don't drink...

00:58:19.504 --> 00:58:21.761
It's at the cafe right up front.

00:58:21.761 --> 00:58:25.479
You and your team are coming, right?

00:58:25.479 --> 00:58:28.930
Even if I don't drink,
I always make it to the after-party.

00:58:28.930 --> 00:58:31.320
That's when a project really feels finished.

00:58:31.320 --> 00:58:32.785
- You have to come.
- Of course.

00:58:32.785 --> 00:58:35.605
- See you later.
- Promise!

00:58:45.726 --> 00:58:46.958
You worked really hard.

00:58:46.958 --> 00:58:48.527
You too.

00:58:48.527 --> 00:58:50.190
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:58:50.190 --> 00:58:52.130
- Great work today.
- Thank you.

00:58:52.130 --> 00:58:54.108
- Oh, here they come.
- Hello.

00:58:54.108 --> 00:58:56.749
Great work today.

00:58:56.749 --> 00:58:59.219
Have a seat.

00:58:59.219 --> 00:59:01.950
You're everywhere I go.

00:59:01.950 --> 00:59:04.240
I'm exactly where I should be.

00:59:04.240 --> 00:59:07.150
Ever think you might be the one butting in?

00:59:07.150 --> 00:59:08.573
Jin Su, here.

00:59:08.573 --> 00:59:10.541
I love company dinners.

00:59:10.541 --> 00:59:12.445
Hey, switch seats with me.

00:59:12.445 --> 00:59:14.289
Mr. Song!

00:59:14.289 --> 00:59:15.670
Where are you going? Over here.

00:59:15.670 --> 00:59:17.747
- No, I...
- I saved you a seat.

00:59:17.747 --> 00:59:19.906
You should join us for a drink.

00:59:19.906 --> 00:59:22.066
Just have one here first,
and you can move seats later.

00:59:22.066 --> 00:59:25.336
Great work today, sir.

00:59:25.336 --> 00:59:27.687
Wait, where is Mr. Lee Eun Ho?

00:59:27.687 --> 00:59:30.064
He couldn't make it today.
Something came up with his child.

00:59:30.064 --> 00:59:31.325
Thank you.

00:59:31.325 --> 00:59:33.671
Thank you.

00:59:36.381 --> 00:59:38.392
- How about a drink, sir?
- I don't drink alcohol.

00:59:38.392 --> 00:59:40.696
Just hold the glass.

00:59:40.696 --> 00:59:42.067
♪ Your glass is filling up ♪

00:59:42.067 --> 00:59:44.924
- One second.
- Drink up.

00:59:44.924 --> 00:59:46.762
Mr. Ji Su, have a drink with us too.

00:59:46.762 --> 00:59:50.098
- Have a seat!
- Do you want another drink?

00:59:50.098 --> 00:59:51.774
Mrs. Na Ri, have a drink too.

00:59:51.774 --> 00:59:53.908
You have to drink on a day like this.

00:59:53.908 --> 00:59:56.088
And...

00:59:56.088 --> 00:59:59.681
- Let me pour you a drink.
- Thanks.

00:59:59.681 --> 01:00:02.125
- Great work today.
- Thank you.

01:00:02.125 --> 01:00:03.222
Alright,

01:00:03.222 --> 01:00:06.069
fill up your glasses.

01:00:06.069 --> 01:00:08.507
Let's meet again soon
on another project, in good health.

01:00:08.507 --> 01:00:10.645
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

01:00:10.645 --> 01:00:12.163
- Thank you.
- Thank you for your hard work.

01:00:12.163 --> 01:00:15.236
Thank you for your effort.

01:00:21.129 --> 01:00:24.575
This is so sweet.

01:00:24.575 --> 01:00:26.894
Let's start the Rabbit Game!

01:00:26.894 --> 01:00:29.066
- Umchi-chi, umchi-chi.
- Umchi-chi, umchi-chi.

01:00:29.066 --> 01:00:31.276
- Bunny, bunny.
- Carrot, carrot!

01:00:31.276 --> 01:00:33.976
Where is Attorney Kang?

01:00:33.976 --> 01:00:36.113
He probably won't come.

01:00:36.113 --> 01:00:38.813
How would you know that?

01:00:38.813 --> 01:00:41.133
Have a drink.

01:00:42.006 --> 01:00:43.883
Everyone except Yu Been, let's raise a glass.

01:00:43.883 --> 01:00:45.240
Sounds good.

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:47.536
This is so fun.

01:00:50.383 --> 01:00:52.207
But Mr. Ji Su,

01:00:52.207 --> 01:00:54.265
what exactly do you do? Are you a bartender?

01:00:54.265 --> 01:00:56.903
Oh, his real job?

01:00:56.903 --> 01:00:58.453
He's an actor.

01:00:58.453 --> 01:01:00.084
Seriously?

01:01:00.084 --> 01:01:01.394
I do theater,

01:01:01.394 --> 01:01:03.418
and I've worked a lot of part time jobs,

01:01:03.418 --> 01:01:05.545
so I picked up things like this.

01:01:05.545 --> 01:01:08.485
I knew it. You've got a different aura.

01:01:08.485 --> 01:01:10.175
Do you have a fan club?

01:01:10.175 --> 01:01:13.935
If not, I'll start one today.
I'll be the president.

01:01:16.035 --> 01:01:17.763
Don't be the president. Be the audience.

01:01:17.763 --> 01:01:19.941
I'll invite all of you.

01:01:19.941 --> 01:01:22.867
- Come see my play.
- I love that!

01:01:23.927 --> 01:01:27.015
- Promise!
- Yeah!

01:01:30.920 --> 01:01:34.187
- You better keep that promise.
- Of course.

01:01:36.183 --> 01:01:39.690
Come on, let's drink!

01:01:39.690 --> 01:01:40.880
Come on.

01:01:40.880 --> 01:01:42.719
You too.

01:01:43.834 --> 01:01:46.834
Drink up!

01:01:46.834 --> 01:01:49.684
Oh, your place is that way...

01:01:49.684 --> 01:01:52.234
So you usually drive on Gangbyeonbuk-ro, huh?

01:01:52.234 --> 01:01:55.682
Gang... Gangbyeon...

01:01:55.682 --> 01:01:58.143
Where exactly is Gangbyeon?

01:02:14.565 --> 01:02:16.863
You usually get drunk after only two drinks.

01:02:16.863 --> 01:02:18.276
Sir...

01:02:18.276 --> 01:02:20.633
How many fingers do you see?

01:02:20.633 --> 01:02:25.259
Hey, when did your hand grow six fingers?

01:02:27.532 --> 01:02:30.013
Hold on.

01:02:30.013 --> 01:02:33.020
I'm going to get some air.

01:02:34.744 --> 01:02:37.204
Be careful.

01:02:39.090 --> 01:02:41.870
Excuse me for a second.

01:02:44.104 --> 01:02:46.224
Let me just...

01:02:54.827 --> 01:02:56.827
Mr. Tae Seop?

01:02:56.827 --> 01:02:58.777
Mr. Tae Seop.

01:02:58.777 --> 01:03:00.187
Hey.

01:03:00.187 --> 01:03:02.940
Are you okay?

01:03:04.455 --> 01:03:07.392
No, I'm not.

01:03:07.392 --> 01:03:09.559
My stomach...

01:03:09.559 --> 01:03:11.756
It feels like it's turning.

01:03:11.756 --> 01:03:12.946
Oh my...

01:03:12.946 --> 01:03:16.030
I'll run and get a hangover remedy.

01:03:16.030 --> 01:03:18.586
Just wait here a second, okay?

01:03:18.586 --> 01:03:21.731
No. Don't go.

01:03:21.731 --> 01:03:22.756
What?

01:03:22.756 --> 01:03:26.652
I mean... you're right here,

01:03:26.652 --> 01:03:28.223
but I can't hold on to you.

01:03:28.223 --> 01:03:31.383
So my stomach keeps turning.

01:03:42.608 --> 01:03:45.081
You can't go.

01:03:57.326 --> 01:04:00.919
So this is your cute drunk side.

01:04:07.626 --> 01:04:09.552
Mr. Tae Seop,

01:04:09.552 --> 01:04:11.975
I'm not going anywhere.

01:04:11.975 --> 01:04:13.260
So...

01:04:13.260 --> 01:04:16.966
you don't have to hold on that tight.

01:04:17.633 --> 01:04:19.339
Oh, okay.

01:04:19.339 --> 01:04:21.972
But Ms. Ui Yeong,

01:04:22.927 --> 01:04:27.667
do you still want to go on that date with me?

01:04:27.667 --> 01:04:31.123
Yes, I do.

01:04:31.123 --> 01:04:33.503
Then...

01:04:34.236 --> 01:04:36.949
do you want to go somewhere

01:04:36.949 --> 01:04:40.222
and have one more drink just the two of us?

01:04:40.222 --> 01:04:43.022
Right now?

01:04:47.054 --> 01:04:49.648
Okay.

01:04:49.648 --> 01:04:52.399
Then I'll quickly grab my bag and come back.

01:04:52.399 --> 01:04:55.919
Just wait here a second, okay?

01:04:57.530 --> 01:05:00.883
Don't go anywhere. Stay right here.

01:05:00.883 --> 01:05:03.604
I'll be right back.

01:05:27.319 --> 01:05:29.965
Mr. Tae Seop!

01:05:32.185 --> 01:05:34.736
Mr. Tae Seop, you can't fall asleep here.

01:05:34.736 --> 01:05:37.020
Wake up.

01:05:37.020 --> 01:05:40.653
It's dangerous to sleep here.

01:05:40.653 --> 01:05:45.006
We said we'd go for another round.

01:05:50.168 --> 01:05:52.841
What is this?

01:06:30.885 --> 01:06:33.632
Where am I?

01:06:33.632 --> 01:06:35.875
Hold on.

01:06:35.875 --> 01:06:39.984
What is this? Why is this black?

01:06:43.188 --> 01:06:44.932
What?

01:06:44.932 --> 01:06:46.483
Oh no...

01:06:46.483 --> 01:06:48.943
Did I sleep with him?

01:06:48.943 --> 01:06:51.763
Did I do it?

01:07:04.424 --> 01:07:07.079
What are you doing?

01:07:07.079 --> 01:07:10.512
What are you doing here? Why are you here?

01:07:19.011 --> 01:07:24.544
What exactly... is going on right now?

01:07:25.402 --> 01:07:30.578
I'm not entirely sure either,
but it seems like...

01:07:34.276 --> 01:07:37.602
something went wrong.

01:07:51.625 --> 01:07:55.376
[Do you want to go on a date with me?]

01:07:59.383 --> 01:08:02.494
[Failed to control my strength]

01:08:03.470 --> 01:08:06.723
[Is anger volatile or something?]

01:08:12.355 --> 01:08:16.075
[No. Don't go]

01:08:18.887 --> 01:08:21.284
According to the witnesses,

01:08:21.284 --> 01:08:24.180
there wasn't just one man.

01:08:24.180 --> 01:08:26.487
There were two.

01:08:26.487 --> 01:08:28.457
This is insane.

01:08:28.457 --> 01:08:30.934
I usually don't meddle
in other people's business,

01:08:30.934 --> 01:08:32.460
but when it comes to you, I keep stepping in.

01:08:32.460 --> 01:08:33.910
Something about this feels off.

01:08:33.910 --> 01:08:35.855
What do you think about the rumors?

01:08:35.855 --> 01:08:37.650
Wait, Ji Su?

01:08:37.650 --> 01:08:40.288
Is he actually close with Son Jeong A?

01:08:40.288 --> 01:08:42.281
Chance of rain, 46 percent.

01:08:42.281 --> 01:08:45.084
I've never seen anyone
prepare this much for a date.

01:08:45.084 --> 01:08:46.775
Do you even know what an opportunity is,

01:08:46.775 --> 01:08:48.699
you clueless guy?

01:08:48.699 --> 01:08:51.117
"Clueless?"